# Update Documentation

When asked to update documentation after code changes, read and follow the skill at `.claude/skills/docs-update/SKILL.md`.

Key points:
- Input is optional. If no git reference or description is given, default to uncommitted changes (`HEAD`).
- **`--no-cache` flag**: Skip git diff entirely and rewrite all sections of targeted docs from scratch by re-reading source code. Can be scoped to a specific path (e.g., `--no-cache backend`). Without a scope filter, refreshes every doc in BOOKMARKS.md (frontend areas, backend, and packages).
- Map changed source files to affected docs using `BOOKMARKS.md` as the index (covers frontend areas, backend, and packages — not all docs in the repo).
- A code change can affect multiple doc types — check overview docs, guides, READMEs, ADRs, and agent rules.
- In diff mode (default), update only the affected sections; do not rewrite unaffected content.
- In `--no-cache` mode, rewrite every section treating the current source code as the single source of truth.
- Show a summary of proposed changes before writing.
